text: "Identify the incorrect pair of UV absorption wavelength with respective compound:",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Tryptophan- 280 nm", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Nucleic acids - 260 nm (N-bases)", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "NADH/NADPH - 340 nm", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Porphyrins - 200 nm", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "**Porphyrins** have a **strong Soret band around 400\u2013420 nm**, not 200 nm. This allows their detection and quantification in biochemical assays.<br><br>**Why other options are correct:**\n**A**. **Tryptophan \u2013 280 nm:** True; aromatic amino acids absorb strongly around 280 nm.\n**B**. **Nucleic acids \u2013 260 nm:** True; nucleobases absorb UV light maximally at 260 nm.\n**C**. **NADH/NADPH \u2013 340 nm:** True; reduced forms of nicotinamide coenzymes absorb at 340 nm.",
