explanation: "In PCR amplification, the amount of DNA doubles with each cycle (exponential amplification).\n<img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/f8218a24-19b5-4e0e-b4e5-0a2981974326.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">the DNA quantity at 25 cycles is approximately half of that at 26 cycles.",
