text: "A 6-month-old infant presents with protuberant abdomen, doll-like facies, and recurrent episodes of hypoglycemia. On examination, there is marked hepatomegaly. Laboratory evaluation suggests Von Gierke disease. What is the primary mechanism responsible for the enlarged liver in this condition?",
