tags: ["PYQ", "NEET PG 2024"],
text: "A patient present with symptoms of dermatitis, diarrhea, and cognitive decline. Which micronutrient deficiency is most likely responsible?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Niacin", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Thiamine", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Pyridoxine", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Retinol", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "The image shows Casal necklace\u2014a photosensitive hyperpigmented dermatitis around the neck, which is characteristic of pellagra due to niacin (Vitamin B3) deficiency.<br><br>Niacin is a precursor of NAD\u207a and NADP\u207a, essential for oxidation\u2013reduction reactions and energy metabolism.<br><br>Deficiency \u2192 impaired cellular energy production, especially in skin, GI tract, and brain.<br><br>Classic triad (3 D\u2019s):<br><br>* Dermatitis (photosensitive, Casal necklace)\n* Diarrhea\n* Dementia<br><br>(+ Death if untreated)<br><br>Why other options are incorrect:<br><br>* Thiamine: Beriberi, Wernicke\u2019s encephalopathy\n* Pyridoxine: Neuropathy, sideroblastic anemia\n* Retinol (Vitamin A): Night blindness, xerophthalmia",
images: [{"url": "https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/questions_image/01KN3TV1KJSW7MCXQRFW081RFG.jpg", "caption": ""}]
