explanation: "Aneuploidy refers to an abnormal number of chromosomes due to nondisjunction during meiosis, resulting in gain or loss of individual chromosomes.<br><br>Examples of Aneuploidy<br><br>* Down syndrome: Trisomy 21\n* Patau syndrome: Trisomy 13\n* Klinefelter syndrome: 47, XXY (sex chromosome aneuploidy)<br><br>Bloom syndrome is not an aneuploidy; it is a chromosomal instability disorder caused by mutation in the BLM gene (DNA helicase) leading to defective DNA repair and increased sister chromatid exchanges.",
