explanation: "* HAT inhibition \u2192 \u2193 histone acetylation \u2192 **chromatin condensation**\n* Associated with **repressive marks (\u2191 H3K9 methylation)**\n* Acetylation = active chromatin; methylation (H3K9me2/3) = silenced chromatin<br><br>Histone acetylation relaxes chromatin and promotes gene transcription, whereas histone deacetylation leads to chromatin condensation and gene repression.<br><br>Effect of Histone Acetylase (HAT) Inhibition:<br><br>* \u2193 Histone acetylation\n* Chromatin becomes more condensed\n* Leads to repressive histone marks, such as H3K9 methylation (H3K9me2/3)",
