explanation: "Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR) is a laboratory technique used to amplify a specific segment of DNA, producing millions of copies from a small DNA sample.\nSequence of steps in PCR<br><br>1. Denaturation (\u224894\u201398\u00b0C)\n    * Double-stranded DNA separates into two single strands due to breaking of hydrogen bonds.\n2. Annealing (\u224850\u201365\u00b0C)\n    * Primers bind to complementary sequences on the single-stranded DNA template.\n3. Extension / Elongation (\u224872\u00b0C)\n    * DNA polymerase synthesizes new DNA strands by adding nucleotides complementary to the template.<br><br>These steps are repeated for multiple cycles, resulting in exponential amplification of the target DNA.",
